elements.summary: A family of partner dances that developed alongside swing-era jazz music, emphasizing improvisation and musicality.

elements.summary: Social partner dance rooted in Afro-Caribbean traditions and popularized through club and festival cultures.
elements.label: Salsa

elements.summary: Partner dance originating in the Dominican Republic, known for close connection and expressive musical interpretation.
elements.label: Bachata

elements.summary: Improvisational partner dance rooted in African American blues traditions, emphasizing connection and individual expression.

elements.summary: Partner dance originating in Angola, emphasizing smoothness and connection.

elements.summary: Disco-era partner dance adapted for club settings.

elements.label: Group Dance

elements.summary: Close-position swing dance developed in Southern California, well-suited to fast tempos and crowded floors.
elements.label: Balboa

elements.summary: Improvisational swing dance originating in Harlem in the late 1920s, often considered the root of many swing styles.

elements.label: Breaking

elements.summary: Club-based dance style rooted in house music culture, blending footwork, groove, and improvisation.

elements.summary: Freestyle dance forms emerging from hip-hop culture.

elements.summary: Expressive club dance originating in disco-era LGBTQ+ communities.

elements.summary: Stylized dance form originating in ballroom house culture.

elements.summary: Rotational partner dance in triple time.

elements.summary: Stylized ballroom adaptation of Argentine tango.

elements.summary: Free-form, nonverbal dance practice typically held in sober, community-oriented settings with DJ-led music journeys.

elements.summary: Therapeutic use of movement for emotional and psychological integration.

elements.summary: Movement practice focused on internal impulse and witnessing.

elements.summary: Technique emphasizing clarity, chance, and independence from music.

elements.summary: Broad family of modern and postmodern concert dance practices emphasizing exploration, abstraction, and experimentation.
elements.label: Contemporary Dance

elements.summary: Early 20th-century rebellion against classical ballet conventions.

elements.summary: Experimental dance movement rejecting formal technique and spectacle.
elements.label: Postmodern Dance

elements.summary: Communal line dance performed at celebrations.

elements.summary: Solo improvisational dance often known as belly dance.

elements.summary: Social and folk dance originating in Colombia.
